# Equicord Components Ruleset

**CRITICAL**: Always use existing components from `src/components/` instead of creating custom UI components. These components provide consistent styling, accessibility, and maintainability.

## Import Path

All components are exported from `src/components/index.ts`. Import them like:
```typescript
import { ComponentName } from "@components";
```

---

## Core UI Components

### ErrorBoundary

**USE**: `ErrorBoundary` from `@components/ErrorBoundary`

**Available features:**
- `ErrorBoundary` - React error boundary component
- `ErrorBoundary.wrap(Component, props?)` - Wrap component with error boundary
- Props: `noop`, `fallback`, `onError`, `message`

**DO NOT**: Create custom error boundaries

```typescript
import ErrorBoundary from "@components/ErrorBoundary";

// Wrap a component
const SafeComponent = ErrorBoundary.wrap(MyComponent, {
    message: "Failed to render MyComponent"
});

// Use as component
<ErrorBoundary onError={(e) => logger.error(e)}>
    <MyComponent />
</ErrorBoundary>
```

---

### Button Components

**USE**: `Button`, `LinkButton`, `TextButton` from `@components/Button`

**Available components:**
- `Button` - Standard button with variants
- `LinkButton` - Button styled as link
- `TextButton` - Text-only button
- Variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `dangerPrimary`, `dangerSecondary`, `overlayPrimary`, `positive`, `link`, `none`
- Sizes: `min`, `xs`, `small`, `medium`

**DO NOT**: Create custom button components

```typescript
import { Button, LinkButton, TextButton } from "@components";

<Button variant="primary" size="medium" onClick={handleClick}>
    Click Me
</Button>

<LinkButton href="https://example.com" variant="link">
    External Link
</LinkButton>

<TextButton variant="primary" onClick={handleClick}>
    Text Button
</TextButton>
```

---

### Card Component

**USE**: `Card` from `@components/Card`

**Available props:**
- `variant` - `normal` | `warning` | `danger`
- `defaultPadding` - Add default padding (auto if no className)

**DO NOT**: Create custom card containers

```typescript
import { Card } from "@components";

<Card variant="normal">
    <h2>Card Title</h2>
    <p>Card content</p>
</Card>

<Card variant="warning" defaultPadding={false}>
    Warning content
</Card>
```

---

### Text Components

**USE**: `BaseText`, `Heading`, `Paragraph`, `Span` from `@components`

**Available components:**
- `BaseText` - Base text component with size/weight/color props
- `Heading` - Heading component
- `Paragraph` - Paragraph component
- `Span` - Inline span component
- Text sizes: `xxs`, `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `xxl`
- Text weights: `thin`, `extralight`, `light`, `normal`, `medium`, `semibold`, `bold`, `extrabold`
- Text colors: `text-default`, `text-muted`, `text-link`, `text-danger`, `text-brand`, `text-strong`, `text-subtle`

**DO NOT**: Create custom text styling components

```typescript
import { BaseText, Heading, Paragraph, Span } from "@components";

<BaseText size="lg" weight="bold" color="text-strong">
    Large Bold Text
</BaseText>

<Heading>Main Heading</Heading>

<Paragraph size="sm" color="text-muted">
    Small muted paragraph
</Paragraph>

<Span size="md" weight="medium">Inline text</Span>
```

---

### Form Components

**USE**: `FormSwitch`, `Switch`, `CheckedTextInput` from `@components`

**Available components:**
- `FormSwitch` - Switch with title and description
- `Switch` - Basic switch component
- `CheckedTextInput` - Text input with validation

**DO NOT**: Create custom form controls

```typescript
import { FormSwitch, Switch } from "@components";

<FormSwitch
    title="Enable Feature"
    description="This will enable the feature"
    value={enabled}
    onChange={setEnabled}
/>

<Switch checked={value} onChange={setValue} />
```

---

### Layout Components

**USE**: `Flex`, `Grid`, `Divider` from `@components`

**Available components:**
- `Flex` - Flexbox container
- `Grid` - Grid container
- `Divider` - Horizontal divider

**DO NOT**: Create custom layout components

```typescript
import { Flex, Grid, Divider } from "@components";

<Flex flexDirection="column" gap="8px">
    <div>Item 1</div>
    <div>Item 2</div>
</Flex>

<Grid columns={3} gap="16px">
    <div>Column 1</div>
    <div>Column 2</div>
    <div>Column 3</div>
</Grid>

<Divider />
```

